{
  "stem": "18575.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Soviet papers, the war, of course, in France, attack on France, we had very little news, except that France capitulated after two weeks of war.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There were some articles, very short one, in the newspapers, the Soviet newspapers about the sea war, between Germans, that the ships were sunk.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, there were two major papers in Soviet Union, one called which is 'truth' in Russian.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The other is which is 'news.' And the joke went around that there is no truth in the news and no news in the truth, which was a fact.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Mostly, the paper were used either as toilet paper, because we're full of propaganda, or as to roll up cigarettes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Russians, the soldiers, used to use the cheapest tobacco called machorka, M-A-C-H-O-R-K, would roll it up into newspapers inside things and smoke it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were all of glory of Stalin and glory of Soviet labor and what a tremendous progress and what a horrible life the capitalists live and all that stuff, and nobody read it.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The attack came in June, 1941.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was unexpected.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was not only unexpected to us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It supposedly was unexpected to Stalin himself, even though he got prior news-- I found out later-- that there will be an attack.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Our town was taken over within three days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was very unexpected.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Just like that it happened and the German army marched in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
